{
  "text": "Wild-type Synechocystis sp. PCC 6803 was grown in BG11 medium [CITATION_1] , and strains carrying constructs in plasmid pPMQAK1 were grown in BG11 supplemented with antibiotics. Cultures were grown at 22\u00b0C under continuous light (\u223c28 \u00b5mol photons/m 2 /s) in flasks (gentle shaking) or in test tubes that were vortexed daily to mix bacterial suspensions. Growth was monitored by measuring optical density OD 730 with Varian Cary 50 spectrophotometer (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA, USA).",
